SIMPLE: collaterally
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Collaterally
<hw>Col*lat"er*al*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Side by
side; by the side.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These pulleys . . . placed <qex>collaterally</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Wilkins.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In an indirect or subordinate manner;
indirectly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The will hath force upon the conscience <qex>collaterally</qex>
and indirectly.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In collateral relation; not lineally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Collateralness</ent>⟦br⟧
